# Cursor Rules — Rahi AI

## First: Read CLAUDE.md
Always read `CLAUDE.md` in the project root before making any changes. It has the full design system, Tailwind theme config, glass utilities, and UI anti-slop rules.

## Code Rules
- React 18 functional components only.
- **Tailwind CSS v4** for all styling. No SCSS. No CSS Modules. No inline style={}.
- Theme variables defined in `src/index.css` using `@theme` and CSS custom properties.
- Dark mode via `.dark` class on `<html>` + Tailwind `dark:` prefix + `var(--*)` theme vars.
- State: Zustand stores.
- Routing: React Router v6.
- Dates: react-day-picker (dark mode styled, no past dates).
- Animations: framer-motion (AnimatePresence for steps, whileTap/whileHover for interactions).
- Font: DM Sans. Never Inter, Roboto, Arial.
- Icons: Emoji for MVP.

## Styling Rules
- Use Tailwind utility classes in className.
- Use custom `glass` / `glass-dark` / `glass-strong` / `glass-strong-dark` utilities for glassmorphism (defined in index.css).
- Use `var(--text-primary)`, `var(--surface)`, etc. for theme-aware colors.
- Use `brand-500`, `brand-400`, etc. for brand color (defined in @theme).
- Glass is for ELEVATED elements only (dropdowns, prompt box, modals). Regular cards use solid `var(--surface)` backgrounds.

## Component Structure
- One `.jsx` file per component. No separate CSS files.
- Components in `src/components/{feature}/ComponentName.jsx`
- Pages in `src/pages/PageName.jsx`

## UI Rules (CRITICAL)
- Follow anti-slop rules in CLAUDE.md.
- Brand orange as ACCENT only — 10-15% of UI.
- Typography contrast: big/small pairings, not everything same size.
- Visual hierarchy: one dominant element per section.
- Glassmorphism on 30% of elements max. Rest = solid backgrounds.

## Don't
- Don't use SCSS, CSS Modules, or any .scss files.
- Don't use style={{}} props (except rare dynamic values).
- Don't install UI libraries (MUI, Chakra, shadcn).
- Don't use placeholder images from external URLs.
- Don't build backend until asked.
- Only modify `PROJECT_SPEC.md` or `MWEB_UI_SPEC.md` when explicitly asked, and keep them in sync with the real implementation.

## Roadmap
- Public roadmap at `/roadmap` (URL-only, no nav entry). Data: `src/data/roadmapFeatures.js`.
- After every feature ship, update `roadmapFeatures.js` per Iteration Learning Protocol (CLAUDE.md): move shipped to `shipped` with `shippedDate`, roll unfinished `building` to `upcoming`, promote 1-2 `upcoming` to `building`.

## Analytics
- Use `posthog-js` via `src/services/posthog.js` (no inline PostHog setup in components).
- Call `initPosthog()` once in `main.jsx` — it already no-ops in Vite dev (`import.meta.env.DEV`) and when `VITE_POSTHOG_KEY` is missing.
- Use the exported `trackEvent(name, props)` helper instead of calling `posthog.capture` directly.
- Only add tracking that reflects real product behavior (no spammy or overly granular events).

## Build Prompts
Reference HOME_PAGE_PROMPTS.md for step-by-step build instructions.
